<h3 id="overview">Overview</h3>
<p>
    Exposes <code>window.customSerializer</code> for registering named <strong>serializer providers</strong> that
    round-trip the structured content model to and from a wire format. The core registry is
    <strong>default-less</strong>: it ships no opinion of its own. Instead a project config selects the platform
    default — the <strong>HTML flavor</strong> — following the
    <a href="/projects/webediting/">Config-Extends-Platform-Default</a> shape (<a href="/backlog/590-graduate-rich-text-editing-the-webediting-project/">#590</a> Fork 6).
    Any editor delegates serialization through the injector chain, so a page ships <strong>one</strong> shared,
    swappable serializer rather than baking a format into the editing surface.
</p>

<h3 id="standards">Web Standards Alignment</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Standard</th><th>Status</th><th>How We Adopt It</th></tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML">HTML serialization</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>The platform-default flavor serializes the model to sanitized HTML and parses it back to the structured pivot.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMParser">DOMParser / XMLSerializer</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>The HTML provider leans on native parse/serialize rather than a hand-rolled tokenizer.</td>
    </tr>
</table>

<h3 id="interface">Interface</h3>
{% highlight "typescript" %}
interface CustomSerializerRegistry extends CustomRegistry<CustomSerializer> {
    readonly localName = 'customSerializer';

    // Register a named flavor (e.g. 'html', 'markdown', 'json-node-tree')
    define(name: string, provider: CustomSerializer): void;

    // The flavor an element should use, resolved via the injector chain.
    // No core default — a project config extends the platform default ('html').
    resolve(forElement: Element): CustomSerializer;
}
{% endhighlight %}

<h3 id="design-decisions">Design Decisions</h3>
<ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 list-disc pl-5">
    <li><strong>Default-less core, platform default in config.</strong> The registry ships no flavor; the project config extends the fully-defined platform default (HTML), per Config-Extends-Platform-Default.</li>
    <li><strong>Registry, not a hard dependency.</strong> Swapping HTML for Markdown or a JSON node-tree is a one-line registration change with zero editor edits.</li>
    <li><strong>Round-trip is the contract.</strong> A flavor must <code>serialize</code> and <code>deserialize</code> losslessly enough to survive an edit cycle.</li>
</ul>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
    Realizes the <a href="/intents/rich-text/">rich-text</a> surface intent. Providers satisfy the
    <a href="/plugs/customserializer/"><code>CustomSerializer</code></a> contract.
    See <a href="/projects/webediting/">Web Editing</a> for the full feature surface.
</p>
